    // The indices are 0, 1, ..., n-1.
    // We check i and its symmetric counterpart n-1-i.

    // The constraints on i are usually 0 <= i < n.
    // If we iterate i from 0 up to n-1, we check every position.

    // Example 1: s = "abcacbd", n=7
    // i=0: s[0]='a', s[6]='d'. 'a' != 'd'.
    // i=1: s[1]='b', s[5]='b'. 'b' == 'b'. Return 1. (Matches example)

